snippet.textDisplay: I am a fully vaccinated (and boosted) adult and believe that this will protect me from serious illness if I contract Covid.  I am also respectful of Novak's concerns about what he decides to put into his body, especially since his regimen is a big part of made him the super athlete that he is today.  I wish that he had just decided to forego the Australian Open when he knew their requirements and that they had not made the medical exemption an option.  I think that on Monday he will be deported and perhaps banned for 3 years.  This will mean that he has only 3 Majors a year to vie for for the remainder of his career.  It will also mean that the Australian Open will be the only major lacking participation from the world's best tennis player, in the final years of his career.  A proper lose-lose scenario for all involved.
